<br>
I read your design over several times.  It certainly looks like you have done you homework, and I like the design as presented, with a few major caveats.<br>
<br>
First:  NTR is the logical best choice for a SSTO with todays tech.  I am curious why you went with a solid core design?  Frankly, Isp in the 900 second range is VERY conservative.<br>
<br>
Second: While you are very conservative on your operating conditions, you state the engine weighs 22,000 pounds and generates 560,000 pounds of thrust.  A thrust to weight ratio of 25 to 1 is REALLY good.  I suppose you have done you figures, and I could see you optimizing this direction given the low Isp target you have.<br>
<br>
Third: This is more of a nitpick, but I thought the specific heat of hydrogen was roughly <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.airliquide.com/en/business/products/hydrogen/index.asp"> 1.4 kilojoules </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> per kilogram?  (I could be reading this wrong....)  This is not a major issue since you have a VERY conservative reactor design from a power standpoint, but if I am not crazy, it would take 70 megawatts to get 10 kilograms of H2 to 2500 C.  I suppose this might have been just a simplifying assumption?<br>
<br>
Fourth: I am curious why you chose a winged design?  Could you not go for a powered flight vertical takeoff and landing design?  That way you do not have to build wings or landing gear, and the mass saved should give you plenty of fuel to get enough delta v to pull this trick off....<br>
<br>
<br>
Also, just to whet your appetite, kindly look at <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://216.239.51.100/search?q=cache:KW2i5369hGwC:www.spacetransportation.com/ast/presentations/1b_meyer.pdf+positron+tungsten+ramjet&amp;hl=en&amp;ie=UTF-8"> this cached page </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> of an Air Force design for an ANTIMATTER SSTO.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Gotta love those wild military guys.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
I have a few thoughts on a Nuclear SSTO, and will post those soon.<br>
