I have posted reference after reference to support my side of this discussion.   You reply with rhetoric, or fling about scare tactics such as your &quot;unshielded 60 reactors&quot; assertion.  The design IS shielded.  It is simply not shielded the way you think it is.   I am surprised you have not stated dramatically &quot;this dangerous and unshielded design produces over 200 gigawatts of power!  How can we even contemplate such a thing!&quot;   Surprisingly enough, I know how many gigawatts it produces.  It doesn't scare me.<br>
<br>
I remain unconvinced of your stance.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
