<br>
Please note that I am NOT advocating a plain gas core reactor, as I wrote clearly in my original design.<br>
<br>
Instead, I advocate using the Nuclear Lightbulb design.  This design fully encapsulates the fission fuel.<br>
<br>
In more detail, this is a dual vortex variant of the gas core design, in which the fuel vortex with the fissile mass is contained inside a silica container, with a second and much larger reaction mass vortex outside the lighbulb.  The radioctive core is fully contained at all times.  I thought I made this design element abundantly clear in my first description.  If there are any other terms you don't understand in my design, please go educate yourself on the web, or simply ask me.<br>
<br>
If you had bothered to read and understand my design before you assumed I was a dangerous nuke-crazy wacko, you might have avoided making a fool out of yourself. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I don't like it when people accuse me of failing to take nuclear hazards into account.  I am pro nuclear, but I have to live here just like you do.  The design is very safe, indeed.<br>
<br>
Is it perfectly safe?   Of course not.  But it is probably much safer than smoking.  Or driving a car.  Or drinking alcohol.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Given the stunning performance level, I think the risk is very much worth it.<br>
